                <article>
                    <!-- article -->

                    <div class="margin">
                        <h2 class="post-title">Set-up a Planned Recording on the SD Card</h2>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">

                      <div>
                          <amp-img on="tap:lightbox1" role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/WebUI-Rec_Schedule.png" width="716" height="746" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img>
                      </div>

                        <amp-lightbox id="lightbox1" layout="nodisplay">
                            <div class="lightbox" on="tap:lightbox1.close" tabindex="0" class="centered">
                                <amp-img on="tap:lightbox1.close" role="button" tabindex="0" src="/images/WebUI-Rec_Schedule.png" width="716" height="746" layout="responsive" class="shadow"></amp-img>
                            </div>
                        </amp-lightbox>

                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                        <table>
                            <tr>
                                <td width="20%">
                                    <strong>Select All</strong>
                                </td>
                                <td>Click here to activate planned recordings 24/7. The planned <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Recording/Video/">video</a> recording and <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Recording/Photoseries/">photo series</a> (<strong>IF ACTIVATED</strong>) will be running continuously.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td width="20%">
                                    <strong>Deselect All</strong>
                                </td>
                                <td>Click here to deactivate all planned recordings. The planned <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Recording/Video/">video</a> recording and <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Recording/Photoseries/">photo series</a> (<strong>EVEN IF ACTIVATED</strong>) will be stopped.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td width="20%">
                                    <strong>Worktime</strong>
                                </td>
                                <td>Click here to activate the planned <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Recording/Video/">video</a> recording or <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Recording/Photoseries/">photo series</a> (<strong>if activated</strong>) during normal working houres.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td width="20%">
                                    <strong>Nighttime</strong>
                                </td>
                                <td>Click here to activate the planned <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Recording/Video/">video</a> recording or <a href="/Web_User_Interface/720p_Series/Recording/Photoseries/">photo series</a> (<strong>if activated</strong>) during the night.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td width="20%">
                                    <strong>Invert all</strong>
                                </td>
                                <td>Invert your selection.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                    <!-- /margin -->

                    <div class="margin">
                        <h3>Set a Schedule for planned Video and Snapshot Recordings</h3>
                        <p>Use the schedule to program planned video or snapshot recordings (e.g. for <a href="http://wiki.instar.com/index.php/Instarvision_2.0_Usermanual_::_Record_::_Photoseries">time-lapses</a>). Every blue box represents 30min of activity. The recorded files will be stored to the camera’ s internal SD card. The filenames will start with a capital “P” to differentiate them from alarm recordings “A” and test images that start with a “T”.</p>
                    </div>
